<br>
If we know for sure every 100 AC equals 10% reduction in damage taken, people will probably go into AC again (assuming a 9K warrior, getting 100 more AC would have the same effect as getting 1000 more HP, and it's probably easier to come up with 100 AC than 1K HP items).  But we do not.  The AC caps remains mostly a mystery to us.  Without knowing how the AC/avoidance/etc works, it's easiest to <br>
go for HP because the effect of HP is very obvious and easy to account for.  If you have 1K more HP it lets you tank that much longer and your CH chains can be that much slower before you still die.   <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=90049">Phantron</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=dagroob>da Groob</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://enmity.net/Public/G.jpg" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 8<br> <font color=#FF0000>(12/10/02 11:59:23 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthearena.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2599.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Why is 100hp such a big deal????</span><hr size=1> Phantron stated the way I feel. I can see 100hp, but I can't see the effect of 10ac, or a couple of saves. That, and when high end tanks have all stats maxed, and rediculous saves and AC, then that pretty much leaves only HP to increase that doesn't have a cap, visible or not. <p><HTML><center>
