<br>
It's like Shaman getting all bent out of shape about their HP numbers and having the wisdom of a drunk troll shadowknight.  You have to do the math, not just look at the pretty numbers.  If Canni IV is 1.8 to 1 mana, and Wisdom is 6 mana to 1 wis, then for that shaman you need to get 10 more HP for every point of wisdom you give up. In other words, if your wisdom (which is common for shaman) is 165 with KEI, you'd need almost a thousand more health to make up for the wisdom you don't have. <br>
<br>
If you don't LEARN the system, you won't ever BEAT the system.  Since no one can say 1 AC protects you by XXXX amount, it's hard to figure out exactly how much HP it's okay to give up.<br>
<br>
I'm convinced though, that if you get your Stamina and AC both as high as you can you'll probably be the happiest.  HP seems to come along for the ride once you get AC and STA up. <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://pub38.ezboard.com/feqtraderscornerfrm38.showMessage?topicID=409.topic"><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://www.eq-viatores.org/sig.php"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--></a><!--EZCODE LINK END--></p><i></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <br><font color=#FF0000>- </font><a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior>The Steel Warrior</a><font color=#FF0000> - </font><a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthearena>The Arena</a> <font color=#FF0000> - </font><a href="http://www.steelwarrior.org">The Steel Warrior website</a><font color=#FF0000> - </font><br><br><table border=0 align=center><tr><td align=center></td><td><img src="http://www.ezboard.com/image/spacer.gif" width=15 height=1 border=0></td><td align=center></td></tr></table><CENTER><!-- START BOTTOM GAMES AD SCRIPT -->
